      },
      "date": "2014-10-08 06:22:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nplease describe the exact case the patch fixes. iirc, MDT doesn't accept new requests till the stack is fully configured.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f26bc89c5a6dde380d44c484fad4db55f1d08b7e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 06:05:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"please describe the exact case the patch fixes. iirc, MDT doesn't accept new requests till the stack is fully configured.\"\n\nAre you sure about this. See lod_obd_get_info, it seems only require one OSP is activate.  See the error message, it seems because the unlink is being handled before all of OSP is added by config log.\n\nLustre: Skipped 3 previous similar messages\nLustre: lustre-MDT0001: Recovery over after 0:04, of 5 clients 5 recovered and 0 were evicted.\nLustreError: 4554:0:(lod_lov.c:698:validate_lod_and_idx()) lustre-MDT0001-mdtlov: bad idx: 4 of 32\nLustre: DEBUG MARKER: /usr/sbin/lctl mark  sanity test_17n: @@@@@@ FAIL: destroy remote dir error 0",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "234bff6bc113b78fbceb05550dd3552a4949666c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-12 06:14:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nthere is the following code to achieve this:\n\nserver_start_targets():\n\n\t/* log has been fully processed */\n\tobd_notify(obd, NULL, OBD_NOTIFY_CONFIG, (void *)CONFIG_LOG);\n        ...\n\trc = dev->ld_ops->ldo_prepare(&env, NULL, dev);\n\nin turn, mdt_prepare():\n\n\ttarget_recovery_init(&mdt->mdt_lut, tgt_request_handle);\n\tset_bit(MDT_FL_CFGLOG, &mdt->mdt_state);\n\tLASSERT(obd->obd_no_conn);\n\tspin_lock(&obd->obd_dev_lock);\n\tobd->obd_no_conn = 0;\n\tspin_unlock(&obd->obd_dev_lock);",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
